pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans=
-serif; color: rgb(165, 165, 165);"><span style=3D"font-size: 13.3333px; te=
xt-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">XHuman origins centered around an eve=
nt known in Human history as the Relakis incident. Relakis was a colony of =
the Humans that underwent strict quarantine due to an accidental release of=
 an intensely painful and fatal virulent laboratory-grown disease. The dise=
ase left millions dead and dying in absolute agony and was nearly impossibl=
e to treat once contracted. The Relakis quarantine lasted many generations =
and was was largely successful at stopping significant spread of the diseas=
e outside of the system.</span></span></p><p style=3D"margin-top: 0pt; marg=
in-bottom: 10pt;"><span style=3D"font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; =
color: rgb(165, 165, 165);"><span style=3D"font-size: 13.3333px; text-align=
: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Relakis was abandoned to its fate. Over time,=
 the few Human persevering survivors began developing genetic immunity to t=
he disease, though they still carried genetic scars from exposure to it.</s=
pan><br></span></p><p style=3D"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;"><span=
 style=3D"text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);"><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(165, 165, 165); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 13.33=
33px;">So intense was the fear of a re-emergence of the Relakis disease tha=
t nearby Human colonies refused to consider re-opening Relakis to any Human=
 contact. The few residents of Relakis who did travel through Human-control=
led&nbsp;space were forced to register and wear encounter suits. They were =
shunned, turned away and branded "Ex Humans" as a slur.</span></span><br></=
p><p style=3D"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;"><span style=3D"font-fa=
mily: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; color: rgb(165, 165, 165);"><span style=
=3D"font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">Defiant, =
the 'Ex Humans' took up this moniker and used it to describe themselves as =
a new race entirely: the history of XHumans began.</span><br></span></p><p =
style=3D"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;"><span style=3D"font-family:=
 Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; color: rgb(165, 165, 165);"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size: 13.3333px; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);">XHumans culture=
 differs from Human society in many ways. XHumans embrace cybernetic implan=
tation, are much more collectivist and have no scruples about polyamory or =
group families. XHumans have fewer inhibitions than Humans, seeing them as =
weak and indecisive.</span><br></span></p><p style=3D"margin-top: 0pt; marg=
in-bottom: 10pt;"><span style=3D"font-size: 13.3333px; text-align: var(--bs=
-body-text-align); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; color: rgb(165=
, 165, 165);">XHumans and Humans find each other detestable. Something abou=
t the extreme familiarity, the very close in looks but also noticeably diff=
erent continues to make each race intolerant of each other.</span><br></p><=
